\section{Multicolumns}

Multicolumns are marked in the same way as LaTeX with the exception that an additional specifier, specifying a class can be optionally inserted \verb+\multicolumn{2}{c,centered}{text}+. This is removed during the LaTeX run.

\begin{verbatim}

\begin{table}[htp]
\begin{tabular}{lllll}
\centering
cell-1 &\multicolumn{3}{|c|}{These are three multicolumn  cells}  &cell-5\\
cell-1 &\multicolumn{2}{|c|}{These are two multicolumn  cells}   &cell-4 &cell-5
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\end{verbatim}

Will render as:

\begin{table}[htp]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{lllll}
cell-1 &\multicolumn{3}{|c|}{These are three multicolumn  cells}  &cell-5\\
cell-1 &\multicolumn{2}{|c|}{These are two multicolumn  cells}   &cell-4 &cell-5
\end{tabular}
\end{table}






